Sentencas: A computational model is presented in which performance of a solid oxide fuel cell with functionally graded electrodes can be predicted.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: The model calculates operational cell voltages at varying electrode porosity and operational parameters, accounting for losses from mass transport through the porous electrodes, ohmic losses from current flow through the electrodes and electrolyte, and activation polarization.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Specifically the physical phenomena that occur when the electrode is designed with a change in microstructure along its thickness are studied.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Cell polarizations are investigated to find arrangements for which the minimal polarization occurs.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Both diluted hydrogen fuel and partially reformed methane streams with internal reforming are investigated.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: It is concluded that performance benefits are seen when the electrodes are given an increase in porosity near the electrolyte interface for certain fuels and with satisfactory material properties.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Enhanced reformation is observed in high tortuosity structures due to increased gas residence time within the electrode.
Titulo: Mass transfer in graded microstructure solid oxide fuel cell electrodes
